111701803242221515344< /user_id>
<review>This hidden gem in Pine Grove is like no other restaurant.  Don't come in a hurry or expecting something bland!  The care and artistry that goes into these dishes can only come from a chef sharing their passion for flavor and home cooking with you.  Charlie (I hope I spelled it right) is such a darling person in addition to being a food genius.  I got the Spicy Korean Soup (asked for it mild, but was warned that's still 5/10 heat without adding anything) and man.  It is a flavor explosion!  The spice was definitely there, but not the kind of heat that drowns iut flavor.  She described to me the array of spices, peppers, herbs, roasted roots, and 8 hour bone broth base that goes into this dish and it's no wonder it's so incredible!  There was some Sichuan pepper in there that I tasted for the first time in my life, and they aren't kidding when they say it makes your mouth tingly!
I hope you will make the trip to try this place, settle in, and get ready for some food artistry and a flavor granade if you give this soup a try.  My other go-to is the Bibimbop.  If you're new to this cuisine, it's great comfort food.<//review></record>

<Time>1620328747548</Time><pics>None</pics><Review>I was surprised when my Mother and Sister selected Wok & Roll Asian Kitchen as the restaurant for our party.  They raved about the food and coming from two respected foodies, I decided to give it a try....
Wow... I was not disappointed... and can say that it is one of the best fusion restaurants in the Bay Area.
We started with a salad that had a special sesame dressing that was out of this world!   Next came the Drunken Egg Plant... which was perfectly fried and sat on sweet soya sauce mixture.  Needless to say these were complemented with delicious Amador white and red wines.
My favorite was the Korean ribs w Kimchi/ginger/garlic lettuce wraps that was so refreshing to the palate.  We then had the coconut chicken curry that had a little heat in it to enhance the sweetness of the coconut and bring out the curry flavors.  My mother liked the fried whole fish with ginger and my sister's was the Drunken noodles.
Ever walk into a restaurant and say man... this place is classy... as exhibited by the dinnerware settings and also the excellent service by Chef Charvy and her husband Colin!
Make sure you make your reservations way ahead as this place is going to fill up fast!< /Review><Name>tony N.< /Name><response>None</response>< rating>

<text>I think their food is outstanding. The pork fried rice is probably the best pork fried rice I've ever eaten, and I think an Asian place's pork fried rice is a good way to judge the quality of an Asian place's food. It has huge pieces of pork and the rice itself is just loaded with flavor. I live up in Pioneer where Le's Chinese is the closet place to me. There is no comparison between these two places. Wok and Roll is so much better, definitely worth the extra drive for me. Plus her weekly specials are good too --- Bao Tacos on Tuesday and Banh Mi sandwiches on Thursday. Pine Grove has some good food with 88 Hamburgers one of my favorite hamburger places, and now Wok & Roll as one of my favorite Asian food places.</text>< name>

Brenda Liu<//user_name>
<Text>Pretty yummy ramen! The soft boiled egg is perfect. The noodles can be a little more chewy, and the chashu is slightly fattier than I like. Overall pretty delicious though!

The place is nice and bright, the wait staff is friendly and keeps the place clean. Solid 4 stars.</Text>< Pictures>
[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN497RqnST8dkdDU_b9Ln15RbZwFY0cBbpGb_ag=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pictures>
</record>

< review>
The decor is amazing, the service is friendly, but the ramen is below average.  I bit into the char-siu (roasted pork) and it was like trying to chew beef jerky.  The broth was creamy and full bodied, and the noodles had a good bite to them, but if you call yourself a ramen  lounge, you have to understand that the roasted pork is supposed to be tender.

We also had their vegan ramen which had a coconut milk based broth which tasted good but felt more like eating a Thai Panang curry rather than a ramen broth.  Also, if your vegan ramen is $15, please include a few more vegetables than a single bok choy and some slices of sweet potato.

I am not difficult to please, if you look at my review history, I enjoy and give great reviews to most places I visit.  This is the lowest review I've given in years and I want to repeat that the service was excellent and that the restaurant looks wonderful.

I can recommend this lounge for anything but the food at the moment.< /review>

< username>
Irene Johnson< /username>
<date>1550203263846< /date><rate>1</rate>< Review>
This place wasn't my first choice to eat but my family agreed to it due to the heavy rain. The original place we wanted to eat was super packed with a long wait, and if it had not been raining, I would have waited. When we walked in, the waitress pointed to a table to sit at with her back turned and that was the greeting we received. Myself, my husband and 2 children sit down. We were first met with a man who simply walked up and said, you want waters, right? I looked at him confused and asked if there was anything to drink other than water and liquor. So he tells us the non alcoholic drinks and before we even finished ordering the drinks, he had already left, leaving my smallest child without even taking her drink order. Luckily another server brought her a drink and then afterwards he returns with the other drinks. The server was a laid back female that I felt was consistent with refills and just all around helpful but once gave us our containers for leftovers, she never came back, not even to bring our check.. We were stuck waiting for 10 minutes until the girl who brought my daughters drink asked if we had been waiting to pay.
The food was terribly over priced and I really mean that. I felt it was the most expensive Top Ramen I have ever eaten. The food was completely bland and I had to use chili paste and soy sauce to give flavor. My husbands ramen was cold, which is amazing because ramen is suppose to be hot. The fried tofu was the only thing good other than the rice and chicken bowl for my smallest child. Everyone ordered something different and everyone was disappointed. Unfortunately I will never come to this place again. The music was good but it was definitely not worth the money I just spent.<//Review>

< Review>
The Ramen Lounge treated me to a wonderland of taste sensations - from the fried tofu appetizer to the Tonkotsu Ramen (extra spicy for me), I couldn't be more pleased. The drinks and Ramen are reasonably priced and you get far more in quality and service than you pay for. I'm shocked by some of the reviews that leave you wondering otherwise. Honestly, do they run a neighboring shop and are afraid of competition? Seriously now! The Ramen Lounge rocks and I'd like to personally check the motives of anyone who says otherwise. Yes, they're new. And with anything new, I'm sure there have been moments where not everything is perfect. But, all-in-all, I'm a fan and can't wait to go back and try more of what the Ramen Lounge has to offer. Def recommend it!</Review>

I'm on my way to trying as many ramen shops in California and have been to a couple dozen so far. This place is pretty good. <user>102809364635888919026< /user><Gmap_id>0x80c33151ce8e5ea9:0x4bb6da0b73e02489<//Gmap_id>< text>
The Vibe: Hip-Hop culture prominently displayed via Posters of RUN DMC + De La Soul + Tribe Called Quest + Beastie Boys & Graffiti Artwork & Black Music heard on heavy rotation with a well stocked BAR & RAMEN to be had.

The Reality: Once I inquired about who the owner of this establishment is AFTER ordering  COCONUT Vegetarian Ramen, the vibe for ME SUDDENLY SWITCHED from a low-energy/eye contact avoiding waitress & a staff member walking out/in the door giving me a "stern glare of concern" as I sat/waited in the RUN DMC Booth reading my book TO a more upbeat & audible waitress & a more relaxed manager! The COOK was even gracious enough to come over to ask about my Ramen. It was DELICIOUS! Had my experience been warmer BEFORE my inquiry, it would've been worth the $16.43 + $2 tip... Simply put, maybe I LOOKED a little TOO hip-hop for the moment. A special thank you to the Young Lady bar tending who is blessed with a beautiful gap-toothed smile & graciously assisted me with my Coconut Ramen + H2O order BEFORE my vibe switching inquiry.<//text>

< Review>
I have been a patient of Dr Dab and his office staff for a number of years and have always been impressed by the professionalism and courtesy of the whole office as well as Dr Dab's approach to dental treatment consisting of offering all dental options and clearly explaining procedures in advance.  During this pandemic I sustained a dental emergency consisting of a broken  front tooth impacting my oral function as well as appearance.  Dr Dab was able to schedule me quickly and the office was well equipped to follow all sanitary guidelines mandated by the pandemic.  He presented me with a conservative approach to the tooth repair and explained in detail why he recommended this as opposed to other possible options.   The procedure was timely and painless and the tooth was back in place within an hour. I was given clear post-procedure instructions including what to look for and how to contact the office if there was a problem.  This particular event is illustrative of all the interactions I have had with Dr Dab and his staff and I am grateful to be in their care.  I highly recommend Dr Dab to anyone seeking dental care.</Review>

< Name>
Elise Souza</Name>
<Date>1616628409575</Date><rate>2</rate>< review>
Reason for 2 stars:

My massage was very painful (and not in the good way.) I did not ask for a deep tissue massage (though that is definitely not what this was) nor did I ask for intense pressure. But my massage therapist was massaging my bones with her knuckles, which is very painful. I did not say anything because I thought perhaps this is what it's supposed to feel like since the reviews were so great. She also seemed a little bothered by my presence, but nothing a smile can't fix.

In addition, I waited for my chiropractor to enter the room for about 40 minutes. Which time goes by very slow when all you can do is wait.

The staff was still lovely & very sweet. But I will not be returning for a massage again in the future.< /review>

<Time>1519969034703<//Time><text>I went in fora few weeks with back pain that was getting worse. I couldn't even stand up straight. I went in again with lower back pain and left leg falling asleep while driving.I drive a stick shift and couldn't feel if I was pushing the clutch in. I  was told I had a herniated disk and would need to come in daily for up to two weeks. Was told not to bend forward, bring my chest over my knees and not to lay on my back with my legs elevated as this would make my condition worse. I asked if it is something they would need to take x rays for and the chiropractor said it was not necessary and he was positive about it being a herniated disk. I asked if I should go to hospital and was told they could not do anything for me but may give me morphine in extreme circumstances. After the 2nd day of going in I was feeling worse after being adjusted. I couldn't even get out of my car. I had a family member drive me to emergency room. They took x rays and said I did not have a herniated disk, it was a pinched nerve and I had sciatica. They gave me an anti-inflammatory shot and a muscle relaxer. After about an hour I felt much better. They gave me stretches to do, everything the chiropractor told me not to do. After 3 days of doing the stretches I felt much better and can bend over fine and was back to work. Instead of missing two weeks of work and needing to pay for 2 weeks of adjustments.
I know sciatica can  be caused by a herniated disk but the physician assistant said the only way to get to that diagnosis is with x rays. I did what the chiropractor told me not to do and feel much better.</text><Rating>1< /Rating><username>Michael Medrano< /username><gmap_id>0x80dc83425a95535b:0x1d1043afc83ca6dc< /gmap_id><pictures>None< /pictures><UserId.>104121727734862180411<//UserId.></record></dataset><record>

I was referred here by a friend who raves about this place, but I was underwhelmed. To start, we came in as a group of 3  and waited about 20 mins to be seated, the second person who was getting a pedicure was left as the services were being started to care for who seemed to be a "regular", the 3rd person waited an extra 15 mins to get her pedicure started even though there were available seats. The gentlemen who was doing my acrylics seemed to be in a rush to service the regular and the finish product of my nails looked like they needed to be filled"as if I had worn them for two weeks" I brought this up to him and he was very rude and tried to discredit my concern. He started to work on the regular until another person in my party said it was inadequate work. All in all we were able to convince him to fix the issue but I would said there needs to be a BIG improvement on communication. The other girls in my group enjoyed my service but I probably won't be coming here again.< /review>

Andre DeLoach< /name>
< Date>
1600311621113</Date>
<Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
Delicious food and great customer service from the store staff.

Some of the best seasoned and lightest falafel I've ever had.

The Byblos Salad is generous in size. It can be shared by two. Very fresh. Make sure to toss the salad with the light dressing. Yum.

The chef, Paco, is proud of the food he prepares and it shows.  And the rest of the staff are friendly and courteous.

And I appreciated that all of the staff were conscientious about wearing their face masks. Thank you!

Outdoor seating is available.  I believe most of their business these days is during busy lunchtime, so the patio is not crowded after 6 PM.  Enjoyed sitting out there as the cooler breezes that blew in.

Definitely going back to get more falafel.  The #12 Falafel Platter...I got my eye on you!!

(This review is posted on Yelp as well.)<//review>

< Review>
I have been a patron for about four years now and always make it a point to stop by when I am driving through or heading to the area. They have been a family owned and operated business that prides themselves on treating their customers like family. The surroundings are simple and modest, with indoor seating and patio seating. They focus on quality food for very reasonable cost compared other similar restaurants. Their dishes are authentic, their meats are fresh and flavorful with great seasoning, and their hummus and tabbouleh on their own are wonderful and makes everything even better! Making a choice to give this restaurant a try not only supports a small business, but I suspect once you do, like I, will consider it a favorite!<//Review>

< Text>
I ordered the chicken kabob platter & was not disappointed. The chicken was moist & flavorful, the rice was cooked just right, the hummus was fresh & authentic tasting, and the tabbouleh wasn't too powerful &  made a great addition to the hummus and pita... My only complaint would be that the pita bread wasn't warm when I picked up my order & it was kinda soggy but I did order take-out so it was wrapped in cellophane.

But all in all, you get a good amount of food for what you pay, the price isn't steep, & it's authentic Mediterranean food with a very fresh taste. I will definitely come back to try other dishes on the menu!< /Text>
